\section*{Axiom Set A: Deterministic Unitary Evolution}

\textbf{Definition 1.1 (Closed System Dynamics):}
Let $\mathcal{H}$ be a Hilbert space representing the closed informational system. The state vector $|\psi(t)\rangle \in \mathcal{H}$ evolves according to the linear Schr√∂dinger equation:

\begin{equation}
    i\hbar \frac{d}{dt}|\psi(t)\rangle = \hat{H}_{sys} |\psi(t)\rangle
\end{equation}

Where $\hat{H}_{sys}$ is the time-independent Hamiltonian of the cognitive model.

\textbf{Corollary 1.2 (Information Conservation):}
For any two states $|\psi_1\rangle$ and $|\psi_2\rangle$, the overlap $\langle \psi_1(t) | \psi_2(t) \rangle$ is constant in time. Information is never lost or created.

\textbf{Constraint:} This set assumes $\hat{H}_{int} = 0$ (No interaction with external observers).

